The paper discusses fair division problems in an online setting, which involves the allocation of resources over time. This suggests that the paper may fall under the category of game theory (cs.GT), which deals with decision-making in strategic situations. Additionally, the paper discusses the development of new mechanisms, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses normative properties, which could fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS) or cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of dealing with an uncertain future, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
